Niger is not a republic but a military dictatorship. Indeed, a republic is, and I quote: "a form of government  form of government with a constitution and whose representatives are elected by the people for a fixed term", but in the case of Niger 🇳🇪, the military came to power by force (they were not elected by the people and, in addition, there are no representatives of the people, since the national assembly has been dissolved). Consequently, Niger is not a Republic …

Résultat de la traduction The official channels of Junior Eurovision 2023 (its YouTube channel and official website) both indicate that the British and German representatives are written in capital letters and not lower case, so we might as well rely on the official channels (which are the most reliable possible sources on this subject) and leave them in capital letters + leave an "English" link to the English Wikipedia page for readers to click on.

Mali's 🇲🇱 government is a military dictatorship because the democratic institutions that represented Mali's citizens (the National Assembly) have been suspended and the military came to power by force rather than through free, democratic elections.

The government of Niger 🇳🇪 is a military dictatorship, since the democratic institutions that represented the citizens of Niger (the National Assembly) have been suspended and the military came to power by force rather than through free and democratic elections.
